**Key updates:** We added a “Skip to main” link (Technique G1)【1†L19-L27】 and ensured focus outlines on all controls (WCAG 2.4.7)【3†L31-L39】. Contrast ratios for text (price, headings) meet ≥4.5:1【6†L68-L72】. The toast now has `role="status"` for screen readers. Thumbnails have `aria-label`. All dynamic content is inserted with `textContent` to prevent HTML injection. The “Share” button uses the Web Share API or clipboard fallback (secure-only APIs, in HTTPS). We preserved existing layout, labels, and static data, and marked where real API calls would go. 

## Test Cases

- **Keyboard Navigation:** Tab through page. *Expected:* Skip link appears first, jumping to main; all buttons and links show focus outline【3†L31-L39】.
- **Contrast Check:** Verify colors with a contrast checker. *Expected:* All text and UI elements meet 4.5:1 contrast【6†L68-L72】.
- **Invalid ID Redirect:** Navigate to `property.html?id=invalid`. *Expected:* Toast “Property not found”, then redirect to listings.
- **Share Function:** Click “Share” on desktop. *Expected:* Fallback copies URL to clipboard and shows toast. On mobile (if supported), opens native share.
- **ARIA/Screen Reader:** With screen reader, activate Share. *Expected:* Toast text announced (via `role="status"`).
- **Link Targets:** Right-click “I'm Interested” or “Back to Listings”. *Expected:* Works normally (same tab); if changed to open in new tab, ensure `rel="noopener"`.
- **Responsive Layout:** Resize narrow. *Expected:* Gallery and details stack vertically (CSS grid adapts).
- **Image Labels:** Inspect `.heroimg` and thumbnail `divs`. *Expected:* `aria-label="Property image"` on hero; consider labelling thumbnails when implemented.

